Na obra Erratum, pares de palavras sao vistas em um campo no qual camadas de
cores incorporam e dissolvem as formas verbais. As palavras sao quase homofonas
e sempre sugerem significados contrastantes. Essas imagens sao pintadas a mao em
um computador que emprega todo um repertorio de rasgos, borroes, arranhoes,
urdiduras, cortes, composicoes, rabiscos, manipulacoes de cores, manchas,
cortes, filtros, goivagens, escamacao, abrasoes, transparencias, inscricoes e
sobrecastas.

 

No catalogo de uma exposicao feita em 1996 em Nova York, uma curadora do
Guggenheim escreveu o seguinte:

 

"Eduardo Kac habita uma cultura digital, o reino em rapido crescimento da
Internet, povoado por "internautas” que se comunicam do outro lado da cerca e ao
redor do mundo via rede de computadores. A serie Erratum de Kac da forma visual
a sua preocupacao com o que ele descreve como a negociacao, em vez de
comunicacao, de significado. A brincadeira de Kac com palavras quase homofonas,
como "faca" e "noite", sugere que o significado nao e inerentemente fixo. O solo
em camadas - de onde as palavras emergem e se dissolvem como um palimpsesto -
renderiza visualmente essa sensacao de instabilidade. "

 

"Through the Looking Glass," in KY/SCnyc, p. 7 (catalogo de exposicao homonima
realizada no National Arts Club, New York, 1996).

I started investing and learning about crypto in 2012 and I’ve been fascinated by this world ever since. When NFT’s came around I was super excited because of the communities that started developing online around projects. I was able to team up with an incredible visual artist FEWOCiOUS for my first NFT drop, My Head In Your Hands in early 2021. 

I have always been passionate about visual artists and putting on new talent, an interest that meshes perfectly with NFTs. The My Head In Your Hands drop featured an original drawing, animation and music. The project became the first NFT drop with a musical artist to ever gross over 1 million dollars, something that I am really proud of. Since then, I have continued to advocate for the crypto space and minted the “Until I Come Home” music video as an NFT on emerging platform Glass.xyz in the end of 2021. 

Now I am here on Sound.xyz and I can’t wait to build a community for my fans and collectors. 

“Tell Me The Truth” is the first song I have written since “I Feel Like I’m Drowning” that really stemmed from my most vulnerable honest self. Last year I moved from LA back home to NYC - the city where I wrote my first EP and album. “Tell Me The Truth” was the first song I wrote when I moved back. NYC just has a darker vibe that always leaks into my music when I am producing in the city. This song is definitely the song I am the most proud of on my new album. -  Two Feet
